Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit is given as 2,638,420.67 and Total Revenue is 5,813,420.67.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (2,638,420.67 / 5,813,420.67) × 100 ≈ 45.36%

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is given as 1,598,438.00.
• Total Debt is taken as Total Current Liabilities, which is 2,110,671.05.
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities = 1,598,438.00 / 2,110,671.05 ≈ 0.757, rounded to 0.76

Thus, the answers are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.36%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "0.76"
  }
}
